H0.text: Which group of around 200 Greek islands in the Aegean Sea includes Andros, Naxos, Paros and Milos. Dodecanese

H1.text: Which group of around 200 Greek islands in the Aegean Sea includes Andros, Naxos, Paros and Milos. Sporades

H2.text: Which group of around 200 Greek islands in the Aegean Sea includes Andros, Naxos, Paros and Milos. Northeastern Aegean Islands

H3.text: Which group of around 200 Greek islands in the Aegean Sea includes Andros, Naxos, Paros and Milos. Κυκλάς

A4.text: The Cyclades includes about 220 islands, the major ones being Amorgos, Anafi, Andros, Antiparos, Delos, Ios, Kea, Kimolos, Kythnos, Milos, Mykonos, Naxos, Paros, Folegandros, Serifos, Sifnos, Sikinos, Syros, Tinos, and Thira or Santoríni.

A5.text: The Cyclades is an island group in the Aegean Sea, southeast of mainland Greece.
